The paper deals with the analysis and construction of polar codes, which are a type of error-correcting codes used in communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves the design and optimization of the codes, which falls under the category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity). The use of the polar spectrum to analyze the weight distribution of the codes suggests a possible connection to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The enumeration algorithm used to calculate the polar spectrum may fall under the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper deals with the practical implementation of the codes, which may fall under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
